              <p style="margin-top: 0.5rem; margin-bottom: 0;">Airbnb requires hosts to accurately represent their accessibility features. Marking a feature your property doesn't actually have can lead to guest complaints, refund requests, and listing penalties. Only check filters for features that are genuinely in place and functional. If you're unsure whether a feature qualifies, err on the side of not checking it and describe what you do have in your listing description instead.</p>
